This paper deals with indexing and querying large datasets, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus is on range aggregate queries, which are often used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) applications. Additionally, the paper mentions comparison with existing learned index structures, which is a topic of interest in machine learning and artificial intelligence.
